column1: How many House seats held by Democrats from congressional districts carried by Donald Trump in 2016 will be won by Republicans in the 2018 midterm elections?

column11: There are 13 House seats held by Democrats from congressional districts carried by Donald Trump in 2016: AZ-01, IA-02, IL-17, MN-01, MN-07, MN-08, NH-01, NJ-05, NV-03, NY-18, PA-08, PA-14, and WI-03 (Center for Politics, NYT, Daily Kos). This question closed as "Between 2 and 4 seats, inclusive" with an end date of 6 November 2018. See our FAQ to learn about how we resolve questions and how scores are calculated.

I constructed an extremely crude Monte Carlo simulation in Excel, which used probabilities from 538's "deluxe" model to determine whether or not a given democratic candidate won. However, it treated the outcome of each election as independent, which simply isn't correct (the odds of one seat being retained by democrats is affected by the general ballot, which also affects other elections).
